keys.description: Select the engine used to evaluate antenna state. The EXT engine uses an external comparator for current measurement. The MADC engine uses a built-in measurement ADC and requires only a shunt resistor for current measurement. The MADC engine is supported only in selected u-blox generation 9 receivers.

MADC.description: Uses built-in ADC and a shunt for current measurement.

keys.name: CFG-HW-SENS_WOM_THLD
keys.description:
Wake-On-Motion threshold
Required acceleration on single accelerometer axis for triggering wake up, from 0 to 1 g, where g = 9.81 m/s^2. Value range is [1-255], with 1 step = 1/255 * g. For example, for 0.5 g threshold the configured value should be 128.

keys.name: CFG-LOGFILTER-APPLY_ALL_FILTERS
keys.description: Apply all filter settings. Set to true when all filter settings are to be applied, not just recording enabling/disabling.

keys.name: CFG-LOGFILTER-MIN_INTERVAL
keys.description: Minimum time interval between logged positions. Minimum time interval between logged positions (0 = not set). This is only applied in combination with the speed and/ or position thresholds. If both MIN_INTERVAL and TIME_THRS are set, MIN_INTERVAL must be less than or equal to TIME_THRS. Note: the value set here does not take effect unless CFG-LOGFILTER-APPLY_ALL_FILTERS is enabled.

keys.name: CFG-LOGFILTER-ONCE_PER_WAKE_UP_ENA
keys.description: Once per wake up. Set to true recording only one single position per PSM on/off mode wake-up period is enabled. Note: the value set here does not take effect unless CFG-LOGFILTER-APPLY_ALL_FILTERS is enabled.

keys.name: CFG-LOGFILTER-POSITION_THRS
keys.description: Position threshold. If the 3D position difference is greater than the threshold then the position is logged (0 = not set). MIN_INTERVAL also applies. Note: the value set here does not take effect unless CFG-LOGFILTER-APPLY_ALL_FILTERS is enabled.

keys.name: CFG-LOGFILTER-RECORD_ENA
keys.description: Recording enabled. Set to true when recording enabled.

keys.name: CFG-LOGFILTER-SPEED_THRS
keys.description: Speed threshold. If the current speed is greater than the threshold then the position is logged (0 = not set). MIN_INTERVAL also applies. Note: value set here does not take effect unless CFG-LOGFILTER-APPLY_ALL_FILTERS is enabled.

keys.name: CFG-LOGFILTER-TIME_THRS
keys.description: Time threshold. If the time difference is greater than the threshold then the position is logged (0 = not set). Note: the value set here does not take effect unless CFG-LOGFILTER-APPLY_ALL_FILTERS is enabled.

keys.name: CFG-MOT-GNSSDIST_THRS
keys.description: Distance above which GNSS-based stationary motion is exit (a.k.a. static hold distance threshold). Set this parameter to 0 for firmware default value or behavior.

keys.name: CFG-MOT-GNSSSPEED_THRS
keys.description: GNSS speed threshold below which platform is considered as stationary (a.k.a. static hold threshold). Set this parameter to 0 for firmware default value or behavior.

keys.name: CFG-MOT-IMU_FILT_WINDOW
keys.description: Averaging window for IMU measurements in noisy setups. Increase this parameter in increments of 20 to improve noise rejection in IMU measurements (valid value is in range [100, 200]). Set this parameter to 0 to turn off this feature.

keys.name: CFG-NAVSPG-USE_PPP
keys.description: Use precise point positioning (PPP)

keys.name: CFG-NAVSPG-USE_USRDAT
keys.description:
Use user geodetic datum parameters
This must be set together with all CFG-NAVSPG-USERDAT_* parameters.

keys.name: CFG-NAVSPG-USRDAT_DX
keys.description:
Geodetic datum X axis shift at the origin
Accepted range is +/- 5000.0 meters.
This will only be used if CFG-NAVSPG-USE_USRDAT is set. It must be set together with all other CFG-NAVSPG-
USERDAT_... parameters.

keys.name: CFG-NAVSPG-USRDAT_DY
keys.description:
Geodetic datum Y axis shift at the origin
Accepted range is +/- 5000.0 meters.
This will only be used if CFG-NAVSPG-USE_USRDAT is set. It must be set together with all other CFG-NAVSPG-
USERDAT_... parameters.

keys.name: CFG-NAVSPG-USRDAT_DZ
keys.description:
Geodetic datum Z axis shift at the origin
Accepted range is +/- 5000.0 meters.
This will only be used if CFG-NAVSPG-USE_USRDAT is set. It must be set together with all other CFG-NAVSPG-
USERDAT_... parameters.

keys.name: CFG-NAVSPG-USRDAT_FLAT
keys.description:
Geodetic datum 1.0/flattening
Accepted range is 0.0 to 500.0.
This will only be used if CFG-NAVSPG-USE_USRDAT is set. It must be set together with all other CFG-NAVSPG-
USERDAT_... parameters.

keys.name: CFG-NAVSPG-USRDAT_MAJA
keys.description:
Geodetic datum semi-major axis
Accepted range is from 6,300,000.0 to 6,500,000.0 meters
This will only be used if CFG-NAVSPG-USE_USRDAT is set. It must be set together with all other CFG-NAVSPG-
USERDAT_... parameters.

keys.name: CFG-NAVSPG-USRDAT_ROTX
keys.description:
Geodetic datum rotation about the X axis
Accepted range is +/- 20.0 milli arc seconds.
This will only be used if CFG-NAVSPG-USE_USRDAT is set. It must be set together with all other CFG-NAVSPG-
USERDAT_... parameters.

keys.name: CFG-NAVSPG-USRDAT_ROTY
keys.description:
Geodetic datum rotation about the Y axis ()
Accepted range is +/- 20.0 milli-arc seconds.
This will only be used if CFG-NAVSPG-USE_USRDAT is set. It must be set together with all other CFG-NAVSPG-
USERDAT_* parameters.

keys.name: CFG-NAVSPG-USRDAT_ROTZ
keys.description:
Geodetic datum rotation about the Z axis
Accepted range is +/- 20.0 milli-arc seconds.
This will only be used if CFG-NAVSPG-USE_USRDAT is set. It must be set together with all other CFG-NAVSPG-
USERDAT_... parameters.

keys.name: CFG-NAVSPG-USRDAT_SCALE
keys.description:
Geodetic datum scale factor
Accepted range is 0.0 to 50.0 parts per million.
This will only be used if CFG-NAVSPG-USE_USRDAT is set. It must be set together with all other CFG-NAVSPG-
USERDAT_... parameters.

GPS week numbers will be set correctly from this week up to 1024 weeks after this week.
Range is from 1 to 4096.

BeiDou Talker ID
Sets the two ASCII characters that should be used for the BeiDou Talker ID.
If these are set to zero, the default BeiDou Talker ID will be used.

Enable compatibility mode
This might be needed for certain applications, e.g. for an NMEA parser that expects a fixed number of digits in position
coordinates.

keys.name: CFG-NMEA-CONSIDER
keys.description:
Enable considering mode
This will affect NMEA output used satellite count. If set, also considered satellites (e.g. RAIMED) are counted as used
satellites as well.

keys.name: CFG-TP-PERIOD_LOCK_TP1
keys.description:
Time pulse period when locked to GNSS time (TP1) in [us]
Only used if CFG-TP-PULSE_DEF=PERIOD and CFG-TP-USE_LOCKED_TP1 is set.

keys.name: CFG-TP-PERIOD_LOCK_TP2
keys.description: Time pulse period when locked to GNSS time (TP2) in [us]

keys.name: CFG-TP-PERIOD_TP1
keys.description:
Time pulse period (TP1) in [us]
This will only be used if CFG-TP-PULSE_DEF=PERIOD.

keys.name: CFG-TP-PERIOD_TP2
keys.description: Time pulse period (TP2) in [us]

keys.name: CFG-TP-POL_TP1
keys.description:
Set time pulse polarity (TP1)
Time pulse period must be an integer fraction of 1 second.
false (0): falling edge at top of second.
true (1): rising edge at top of second.

keys.name: CFG-TP-POL_TP2
keys.description: Set time pulse polarity (TP2)

keys.name: CFG-TP-PULSE_DEF
keys.description: Determines whether the time pulse is interpreted as frequency or period

keys.name: CFG-TP-PULSE_LENGTH_DEF
keys.description: Determines whether the time pulse length is interpreted as length [us] or pulse ratio[%]

keys.name: CFG-TP-SYNC_GNSS_TP1
keys.description:
Sync time pulse to GNSS time or local clock
(TP1)
If set, sync to GNSS if GNSS time is valid otherwise, if not set or not available, use local clock.
Ignored by time-frequency product variants, which will attempt to use the best available time/frequency reference (not
necessarily GNSS).
This flag can be unset only in Timing product variants.

keys.name: CFG-TP-SYNC_GNSS_TP2
keys.description: Sync time pulse to GNSS time or local clock (TP2)

keys.name: CFG-TP-TIMEGRID_TP1
keys.description:
Time grid to use (TP1)
Only relevant if CFG-TP-USE_LOCKED_TP1 and ALIGN_TO_TOW_TP1 are set.
Note that configured GNSS time is estimated by the receiver if locked to any GNSS system. If the receiver has a valid
GNSS fix it will attempt to steer the TP to the specified time grid even if the specified time is not based on information
from the constellation's satellites. To ensure timing based purely on a given GNSS, restrict the supported constellations
in CFG-SIGNAL-*
See Table 50 below for a list of possible constants for this item.

keys.name: CFG-TP-TIMEGRID_TP2
keys.description: Time grid to use (TP2)

keys.name: CFG-TP-TP1_ENA
keys.description:
Enable the time pulse (TP1)
if pin associated with time pulse is assigned for another function, the other function takes precedence.
Must be set for frequency-time products.

keys.name: CFG-TP-TP2_ENA
keys.description: Enable the second time pulse

keys.name: CFG-TP-USER_DELAY_TP1
keys.description: User-configurable time pulse delay (TP1) in [ns]

keys.name: CFG-TP-USER_DELAY_TP2
keys.description: User-configurable time pulse delay (TP2) in [ns]

keys.name: CFG-TP-USE_LOCKED_TP1
keys.description:
Use locked parameters when possible (TP1)
If set, use CFG-TP-PERIOD_LOCK_TP1 and CFG-TP-LEN_LOCK_TP1 as soon as GNSS time is valid. Otherwise if not valid
or not set, use CFG-TP-PERIOD_TP1 and CFG-TP-LEN_TP1.

keys.name: CFG-TP-USE_LOCKED_TP2
keys.description: Use locked parameters when possible (TP2)
